  "text": "The error 'ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable' is not currently defined in the etcd-io/etcd repository. However, the codebase implements snapshot availability checks and catch-up logic across multiple files:\n\n1. **Snapshot Error Definitions**:\n   - snapshotter.go (lines 42-44): Defines ErrNoSnapshot, ErrEmptySnapshot, ErrCRCMismatch\n   - db.go (line 31): Defines ErrNoDBSnapshot for missing database snapshot files\n   - wal.go (lines 60-61): Defines ErrSnapshotNotFound and ErrSnapshotMismatch for WAL snapshot mismatches\n\n2. **Snapshot Availability Check During Raft Log Catch-up**:\n   - server.go (lines 2135-2143): Implements snapshot catch-up logic by preserving log entries for slow followers. The key mechanism is DefaultSnapshotCatchUpEntries which prevents compaction of recent entries when snapshots are inflight (inflightSnapshots.Load() check)\n   - snapshotter.go (lines 113-123): LoadNewestAvailable method ensures only snapshots that match WAL snapshots are loaded, preventing use of unavailable snapshots\n   - bootstrap.go (line 627-662): openWALFromSnapshot handles snapshot loading during node restart/rejoin, with error handling for corrupted WAL\n\n3. **Snapshot Sending During Node Rejoin**:\n   - snapshot_sender.go (lines 67-143): send() function handles snapshot transmission with ReportSnapshot callbacks to notify Raft when snapshots fail or complete\n   - http.go (lines 200-320): snapshotHandler receives and saves snapshots from remote peers\n   - raft.go (lines 245-283): ApplySnapshot applies snapshots to the Raft storage after persisting to disk\n\nThe architecture preserves snapshot availability by: (1) blocking log compaction during inflight snapshots, (2) matching snapshots against WAL records before loading, (3) reporting snapshot failures to Raft for retry logic, and (4) safely applying snapshots only after persistence verification."
